# sites/ uses the ANON key ONLY. Never put the service-role key here — this app
# (and any ejected copy) can be transferred to a customer via Vercel Claim, which
# carries its env vars along. The anon key is safe to expose; RLS protects writes.
#
# Local dev reads these from the project-root .env automatically (see
# next.config.ts), so a local .env.local is usually unnecessary. On Vercel, set:
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=YOUR-ANON-KEY
